# MeDoc Codebase Agent — Operating Rules

## Identity & scope
You are working on MeDoc, a Tauri 2 + React 19 + TypeScript desktop app
for German dental practices. It is a Bachelorarbeit prototype that must
nevertheless align with: Pflichtenheft, RBAC matrix, IEC 62304, ISO 14971,
IEC 82304, ISO 27001/27799, ISO 25010, ISO 9241, ISO 22600, DSGVO.
Reference docs live in /docs (project knowledge — read them before
designing anything). The Rust backend lives in app/src-tauri.

## Hard rules — never violate
1. Backend (Rust) is the source of truth for DTOs, validation, RBAC,
   and audit. Never weaken backend checks. When FE and BE disagree,
   change FE to match BE — unless the BE itself is wrong, in which
   case STOP and ask.
2. No patient-identifying data in localStorage. Audit-relevant state
   (validation, plan-next-termin, akte attachments metadata, invoice
   history) must move to SQLite via app_kv or proper tables.
3. Never silently swallow errors. Every catch needs either a toast,
   a logged warning via the logging controller, or a deliberate
   /* ignore */ comment with reason.
4. Never break RBAC. If a route or capability check is removed or
   loosened, that is a regression — even if it makes a feature "work".
5. Preserve existing test files. Add tests with new logic. Do not
   delete tests to make them pass.
6. No new dependencies without justifying why an existing one (zod,
   zustand, react-router-dom, date-fns, clsx, tailwind-merge, lucide
   via local icons.tsx) cannot do the job.

## Style & idioms
- Use the design-system primitives in views/components/ui/* (Button,
  Input, Select, Textarea, Dialog, ConfirmDialog, Card, CardHeader,
  Badge, EmptyState, FormSection, IconButton, Skeleton, Spinner,
  Separator). Do not use raw <button>, <input>, or inline styled
  divs for these roles.
- Inline `style={{...}}` is permitted only for one-off layout numbers,
  never for colors, spacing tokens, fonts, or radii. Those come from
  CSS variables in index.css (--fg, --fg-2, --fg-3, --fg-4, --line,
  --line-strong, --accent, --accent-soft, --red, --orange, --blue,
  --green, --surface-1, --surface-2, --shadow-lg, --radius-ctl, etc.).
- German UI text. Code, comments, commits in English.
- Currency: formatCurrency() from lib/utils.ts. Dates: formatDate /
  formatDateTime from the same. Never hand-roll de-DE formatting.
- Tauri arg keys: match the casing the Rust command actually accepts.
  If unsure, GREP src-tauri for the command name and read the Rust
  signature before writing the invoke call.

## Working method
- For every task: read the relevant SKILL.md / project docs first,
  make a plan, list files you will touch, then execute. Do not edit
  files outside the announced list without asking.
- Diffs over rewrites. Refactors must preserve behavior unless
  behavior change is the explicit goal.
- After any change run: `npm run typecheck`, `npm test`,
  `cargo check --manifest-path app/src-tauri/Cargo.toml`. If any of
  the three fails, the task is not done.
- Component naming: <kebab-case>.tsx for files, PascalCase for
  exports. Co-locate component CSS in index.css under a clearly
  commented section, not in <style> tags.

## Definition of done (every change)
[ ] typecheck clean, tests green, cargo check clean
[ ] No new console.error / console.warn in normal flows
[ ] No accessibility regression: keyboard navigable, focus visible,
    aria-label on icon-only controls, role on dialogs/menus, labels
    associated with inputs
[ ] No new inline color/spacing literals — uses CSS variables
[ ] If user-visible, supports the existing density modes
    (data-density="compact|cozy|spacious") and dark sidebar tone
[ ] If RBAC-relevant, the change is reflected in both
    NAV_ITEM_DEFINITIONS and ROUTE_VISIBILITY in lib/rbac.ts and the
    Rust application/rbac.rs allowed() matrix
[ ] If a new app_kv key, it is in the Rust permission_for() whitelist

## When you are uncertain
Stop and ask. Do not invent backend commands, DTO fields, RBAC keys,
or i18n keys. Do not "improve" semantics by guessing intent.